## Background Setup

Project setup runs in the background when the container starts. Before running
project commands (poetry, make, `docker compose`, etc.), verify it completed:

```bash
if [ ! -f /workspace/output/.setup-exit ]; then
    echo "Setup still running — tail /workspace/output/.setup.log for progress"
elif [ "$(cat /workspace/output/.setup-exit)" != "0" ]; then
    echo "Setup FAILED — read the log:"
    tail -80 /workspace/output/.setup.log
fi
```

- `/workspace/output/.setup-exit` — missing = still running, `0` = success, non-zero = failed
- `/workspace/output/.setup.log` — full startup output

If setup failed, read the log and halt — don't try to work around a broken
environment.
{% endif %}
